Parliament, Monday, 26 August 2019 – The Portfolio Committee will this week conduct an oversight visit to the Department of Public Enterprises and a number of state-owned enterprises (SOEs), including South African Airways, South African Express, Denel and Transnet in Gauteng. The purpose of the visit is for the committee to familiarise itself with SOEs’ operational sites, most of which are experiencing serious challenges relating to governance and financial sustainability, and are also adversely affected by corruption and malfeasance. Framework for oversight visit 27 – 30 August 2019 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC ENTERPRISES, MR KHAYA MAGAXA. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Felicia Lombard (Ms)
